{
    "name": "Overload Pulse Survival — 250 W for 8 s",
    "description": "Heavy short pulse on a moderate sink. Steady-state would burn the part, but the pulse is short enough that the lumped thermal mass keeps the peak under the junction limit. Answers \"Will this pulse survive?\" and \"How much cooldown do I need?\"",
